Posted Salary Range: USD $108,310.00 - USD $140,703.00 /Yr.

Bayut is the number one property portal in the Kingdom, connecting millions of users across the country. We are committed to delivering the best online search experience. As part of Dubizzle Group, Bayut is alongside some of the strongest classifieds brands in the market. With a collective strength of 10 brands, we have more than 200 million monthly users that trust in our dedication to providing them with the best platform for their needs.

As the Facility Coordinator, you will be responsible for overseeing maintenance, cleaning, and security for the building on a daily basis. You will also be responsible for managing the overall resource supply in the office. You will have to coordinate with internal and external stockholders and solve matters related to material delivery.

**Key Responsibilities**

●       Oversee day-to-day facility operations, including maintenance, repairs, and space utilization;

●       Supervise the Maintenance Work, Sub-Contractors, etc;

●       Check devices and structure systems, such as Fire Alarms, CCTV, HVAC, etc, on a regular basis;

●       Respond to emergency calls, if any;  ready and able to attend to the site whenever

●       needed , such as events, Emergencies , Visits, ..etc ).

●       Supervise the cleaning crew and security crew & their daily tasks;

●       Ensure the building meets the safety & health standards and complies with all legal requirements;

●       Provide Support for Both  Soft & Hard Services; supervision all soft Services ( non technical

●       parts , such as cleaning , security , reception , ..etc ) and the Hard Services ( the technical parts such as HVAC , Electrical , CCTV, ..etc )

●       Receive the materials supplied by the vendor as per the purchase order placed by the Purchase Department;

●       Check the materials thoroughly for quality, quantity, specification condition, etc;

●       Store the materials category-wise in appropriate locations;

●       Maintain optimal stock levels;

●       Periodically verify the stock and ensure the availability of stock at all times;

●       Issue materials/assets to the departments/employees as per the material issuance requests;

●       Maintain a record of all assets handed over;

●       Action on the disposal of scrap materials as per the procedure;

●       Maintain all the documents related to the material supplies up to date;

●       Generate reports related to material supplies up to date and submit them to relevant authorities;

●       Participate in audits conducted by internal or external auditors;

●       Ensure the cleanliness and organization of the storeroom.

●     Implement necessary measures to ensure the proper care and preservation of materials.

**Requirements**

**Qualifications**

●       High School or Diploma.

**Experience**

●       3-4 years experience in Facilities & Supervision.

**Knowledge**

●       Supervision experience in Maintenance; should have the main knowledge in maintenance , market , spare parts , Cleaning , ..etc

**Skills**

●       Leadership and Team Management;

●       Communication Skills;

●       Organizational Skills;

●       Problem-solving Skills;

●       Safety Management.

●       Good Bookkeeping skills.

●       Comprehensive knowledge of managing inventory;

●       Familiar with common inventory terms;

**Traits**

●       Honest, Helpful, Focused and Flexible.

**Benefits**

* High-performing and fast-paced work environment

* Comprehensive Health Insurance
* Rewards and recognition

* Learning & Development

